{"version": 2, "width": 130, "height": 38, "title": "intelnav \u2014 first run, end to end", "env": {"SHELL": "/bin/bash", "TERM": "xterm-256color"}, "idle_time_limit": 1.5}
[1e-06, "o", "\u001b[2;36m# fresh install \u2014 no config, no identity, no models on disk\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.000103, "o", "\u001b[1;38;5;243m$ \u001b[0m\u001b[37mintelnav\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.467362, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1mIntelNav requires every peer to contribute.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\nYour hardware is plenty for hosting. \u001b[1mPlease host a slice.\u001b[0m\r\nThe network only works because capable peers commit their hardware.\r\n\r\n  Suggested:  \u001b[32mQwen 2.5 \u00b7 0.5B \u00b7 Instruct\u001b[0m  layers [0..6)\r\n\r\n  How to host:\r\n    \u001b[1mINTELNAV_RELAY_ONLY=1 intelnav\u001b[0m   (one-time, to reach the TUI)\r\n    Inside the TUI: \u001b[1m/models\u001b[0m \u2192 highlight a row \u2192 press \u001b[1mc\u001b[0m\r\n    Then \u001b[1m/service install\u001b[0m to make it permanent across reboots.\r\n\r\n"]
[1.468036, "o", "\r\n"]
[1.468058, "o", "\u001b[2;36m# the gate gives two paths. relay first to reach the TUI:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.068128, "o", "\u001b[1;38;5;243m$ \u001b[0m\u001b[37mINTELNAV_RELAY_ONLY=1 intelnav\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.600434, "o", "\u001b[?1049h\u001b[?2004h"]
