[140.372176, "o", ";230;230;49mThe answer to \"17 squared\" (written as \\( 17^2 \\)) is **289**.\u001b[23;7H\u001b[39;49m                                                                              \u001b[24;7H\u001b[38;2;230;230;230;49mIn mathematics, squaring a number means multiplying it by itself. For example:\u001b[25;7H\u001b[39;49m                             \u001b[26;12H\u001b[38;2;230;230;230;49m5^2 = 5 \\times 5 =\u001b[26;31H25 \\)\u001b[39;49m      \u001b[27;7H\u001b[38;2;230;230;230;49m- \\( -3^2 = (-3) \\times (-3) = 9 \\)\u001b[28;7H\u001b[39;49m                                                                                                                       \u001b[29;7H\u001b[38;2;230;230;230;49mSo for any number, whether positive or negative, the square of that number is simply its numerical value multiplied by \u001b[30;7Hitself.\u001b[31;1H\u001b[39;49m                                                                                                                                  \u001b[32;1H\u001b[38;2;136;136;136;49m\u250c commands \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500"]
